checks every pull request must pass, and see how releases are cut.</p>
<h2 id="developer-certificate-of-origin">Developer Certificate of Origin</h2>
<p>Every commit must be signed off under the
<a href="https://developercertificate.org/">Developer Certificate of Origin</a>
 — it
certifies you wrote the patch or otherwise have the right to contribute it. Add
the sign-off automatically with:</p>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell"><span class="line"><span class="cl">git commit --signoff
</span></span></code></pre></div><p>This appends a <code>Signed-off-by: Your Name &lt;you@example.com&gt;</code> line to the commit
message. The DCO check on each pull request enforces it; unsigned commits block
the merge. Amend an existing commit with <code>git commit --amend --signoff</code>.</p>
]]></content><category scheme="https://stageset.projects.metio.wtf/tags/contributing" term="contributing" label="contributing"/><category scheme="https://stageset.projects.metio.wtf/tags/development" term="development" label="development"/><category scheme="https://stageset.projects.metio.wtf/tags/dco" term="dco" label="dco"/></entry></feed>